caption: Smelled great and food looked very delicious from the see through glass when you walk into the seafood city. Ordered the chicken BBQ which was good. Ordered some grilled squid, eh it was okay, when I took the food home I made sure to cook it a bit more because it was kind of not prepared well to eat. Other than that the staff were quick and efficient when serving the food for take out.

This restaurant is my number one restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I love it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. Whenever  I want to go to a good meal, this is the place that comes immediately to my mind. outstanding and diverse  food and a rich menu.well mannered staff members, and pleasant spirit. Not less important, the charge is modest. I tell about this restaurant with pleasure.

Great if you are in the mood for trying Filipino cuisine but everything is a bit overpriced. Even their weekly specials have nothing special about saving money. Very authentic food I have to admit, in fact some of their dishes might not be appetizing to non-Filipinos like me but I consider that a plus. Service is ok and the atmosphere is perfect since you can also eat anything you buy at the other food places there.
The meals and service were beyond my expectations. We really liked the vibes of this restaurant. Amazing restaurant to take my family out for lunch.

Very sub-par food offerings.  The meats can be on the dry side and often look as if they have sat in the warmer all day.  Save your hard earned dollars and go to Subo Filipino Kitchen or Isla Filipina.

This place is my number one place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. Whenever  I I need a decent supper, this is the place that comes straight to my head.  Great and all kinds of  food and a rich menu.generous team, and pleasant vibes. Also important, the price is honest. I tell about this place with pleasure.

Good place to eat but the service is bad. People that works there are very unprofessional. They still bring the Filipino mentality. No hello no good morning or afternoon at all. I call around 10:am to order for the holidays the machine say They are close but they open at 8:00am. If someone does answer no greeting all they say is hello. I have to ask if this is seafood city. The person that answer the phone would say anong gusto mo? Very rude and the management should train them to have a good customer service. Also every thing is so expensive. The barbecue use to be $2.00 a piece now it’s $4.00.
They are slow to take and make orders, desperately needs new management....
Good food but the WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE

We tried their $30 assorted meat platter (I forgot what it's called) and we were very satisfied! We took home the rest because we weren't able to finish it. I was never a fan of Inasal chicken because I didn't like how it tasted but their recipe is really good. There's a lot of parking space too. Their coffee jelly was good, they included nata de coco and other jellies, which I don't like since I'd just prefer coffee jelly in that drink. Employees were really busy but they were still nice and friendly, not grumpy compared to other busy restaurants. Overall, we really liked our experience here.

I always go to Seafood City for Grill City's BBQ (pork/chicken). It's cheap and the sauce is just on point. I was disappointed with their party tray option though. We ordered their rolled lechon and the skin was nothing close to crispy, it was like chewing a rubber. I do recommend this place to my non-asian friends to try out their Filipino BBQ.

Always like to try out Grill City whenever they have a location in the city I am visiting. However, thus far, this is the worst Grill City I have been. Their pork and chicken barbecue are definitely lacking compared to the other locations I have visited. Considering that their barbecue is what they are known for, this place just quite doesn't have the taste or consistency other locations have when it comes to their sauce. Their barbecue is also overcooked and almost too tough to eat. I also asked one of the staff if they have Bulalo, which was posted on their signs all across the market. However, the person doesn't even recognize what Bulalo was. I had to explain what kind of dish it was, but the only response I received was a puzzled look. I would recommend management to train their staff better particularly with regards to their restaurant's menu. Lastly, the main line and dining area should be kept clean at all times. I saw numerous times where the garbage trolley was parked right next to the main line where food was being stored and served. There was also a lot of trash around the dining area. This place has lots of potential. However, management has a lot of work to be done in running it.
Amazing variety of food and a fantastic grocery store.
Quality food quick with a good selection and reasonable prices.
